## [1] "Note that these are mean values for 1000 replicates. However, NA values are excluded. Thus, when the number of random amplifications is 1, the F1-score is almost always NA, but in the rare case that it hits a gene with a true amplification, the F1-score is 30%. This is why the F1-score is higher the lower the number of random amplification calls is."
